"children":[
"Gastric Cancer"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s3_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ae43ef",
"children":[
"Most patients have locally advanced or metastatic disease at diagnosis. The most common symptoms are abdominal pain, anorexia, bleeding, dysphagia, nausea, and weight loss."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s3_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ef8388",
"children":[
"The initial diagnostic procedure is upper endoscopy. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"positron emission tomography",
"children":[
"PET"
]
},
"-CT scans are used to identify the presence of regional and metastatic disease."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e8aa52",
"children":[
"Always obtain upper endoscopy and biopsy in a patient with “achalasia” to rule out gastric cancer."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_on_s3_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4640f1",
"children":[
"Surgery is the primary treatment for locoregional disease. Survival is improved with chemotherapy or combined chemotherapy and radiation therapy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"114349",
"children":[
"Up to 25% of gastric cancers overexpress the ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"HER2"
]
},
" growth factor receptor. In these patients with metastatic disease, add trastuzumab."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"27d6b9",
"children":[
"Use antibiotic and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
" therapy for early-stage ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"MALT"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"lymphoma"
]
},
" of the stomach and evidence of ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Helicobacter pylori"
]
},
" infection."
]
}
]
}
]
},
